Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.57,0:01:35.81,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo and his friends have set out for\NAizen's headquarters, Las Noches.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.93,0:01:38.05,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,But they are dragged into\Nthe Forest of Menos
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.09,0:01:40.61,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,by Runuganga,\Nthe Guardian of the White Sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.33,0:01:44.85,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,In the forest, Rukia is separated\Nfrom Ichigo and his friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.01,0:01:47.77,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,She is saved by Ashido,\Na mysterious Soul Reaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.09,0:01:53.65,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Long ago, Ashido followed Hollows\Ninto the Forest of Menos.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.81,0:01:57.73,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,He fought Hollows by himself\Nfor many years.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.85,0:02:01.21,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Save your...friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.77,0:02:08.85,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Ashido!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.65,0:02:15.89,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo and his friends are able to make it\Nback to the surface with Ashido's help,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.93,0:02:18.57,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,and they finally make it\Nto Las Noches.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.81,0:02:23.81,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Your friends have\Nentered Hueco Mundo.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.89,0:02:26.89,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.69,0:02:29.77,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,“Why,” you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.00,0:02:34.00,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,They've come to save you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.40,0:02:39.53,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Aside from that...\NThey have no other reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.13,0:02:45.77,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,They came to save me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.37,0:02:48.17,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.21,0:02:53.89,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,But that no longer\Nhas any meaning for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.19,0:03:03.09,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,By wearing that, it means you are\None of us in body and soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.60,0:03:09.76,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s the reality, Orihime Inoue.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.84,0:03:13.44,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.84,0:03:20.92,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me. Who does\Nyour body and soul belong to?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.92,0:03:23.72,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.76,0:03:28.76,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Aizen and his desires.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.64,0:03:37.64,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Did we break through it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.84,0:03:40.36,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like it…\NWind is passing through.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.96,0:03:46.16,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.12,0:03:50.88,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,The entrance is just\Na three-day walk in that direction!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.12,0:03:53.88,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot… This isn't a friend's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.32,0:03:56.08,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't go in through the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.64,0:03:59.24,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have the time\Nto walk for three days either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.24,0:04:00.84,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Nel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.92,0:04:05.88,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for bringing us this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.16,0:04:09.32,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you involve yourselves\Nwith us any more,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.36,0:04:11.16,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,you'll wind up being\Ntreated as traitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.96,0:04:13.56,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.52,0:04:16.12,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Later!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.76,0:04:24.28,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait, Ichigo!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.48,0:04:26.68,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.04,0:04:34.24,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.84,0:04:43.28,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,We were traitors from the moment\Nthat Lord Runuganga saw us together!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.64,0:04:46.36,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,No… It may have\Nbeen far before then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.76,0:04:55.16,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Aizen may have already known!\NLord Aizen will never forgive us for that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.44,0:05:03.04,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if Lord Aizen forgives us,\Nthe Espada won't!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.48,0:05:08.36,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Nel is not saying that Nel\Nwants you to take us with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.72,0:05:11.16,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Nel is just telling you this\Nso you don't get worried about us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.20,0:05:13.04,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,What is she saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.28,0:05:14.96,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,I think she wants him\Nto be worried about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.40,0:05:20.84,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Nel is not saying that Nel\Nwants you to take us with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.88,0:05:25.32,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Nel’s not saying that!\NNel’s not saying that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.68,0:05:27.72,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,– Nel’s not saying that!\N– Aww… Jeez. All right…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.56,0:05:33.16,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.64,0:05:35.04,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Her voice is getting fainter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.84,0:05:38.04,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that\Nshe fell underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.52,0:05:40.92,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Fell? What do you mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.20,0:05:43.52,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Wait, Ichigo!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.84,0:05:48.84,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Nel!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.88,0:05:53.68,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow ow…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.72,0:05:54.92,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,That hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.96,0:05:56.20,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,That hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.76,0:05:58.32,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s my line!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.92,0:06:01.52,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you fools doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.60,0:06:04.36,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah! Where's Nel?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.88,0:06:08.00,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,We just came here after Nel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.24,0:06:09.40,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.80,0:06:12.52,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Then where is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.64,0:06:13.88,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo! Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.40,0:06:20.52,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.60,0:06:22.04,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,The floor fell through?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.28,0:06:26.68,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,No… It's probably some airshaft\Nor something that was in the walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.56,0:06:29.80,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like she fell through here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.40,0:06:32.04,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,She sure is a lot of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.96,0:06:36.28,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Hueco Mundo sure\Nhas a lot of holes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.48,0:06:37.72,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Nel!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.80,0:06:39.88,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.24,0:06:40.84,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.52,0:06:42.72,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.88,0:06:44.68,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we can't leave her alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.44,0:06:48.12,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez. What troublesome guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.64,0:06:49.76,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Good grief…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.28,0:06:51.28,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.68,0:07:02.84,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo, you idiot! Baldy!\NPiece of crap! Good-for-nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.88,0:07:04.40,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's a good-for-nothing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.28,0:07:07.80,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Why did you come?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.96,0:07:10.88,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Nel doesn't really want you\Nto take me with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.44,0:07:14.08,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Aw… I'm getting kind of annoyed…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.48,0:07:15.88,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll really leave you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.00,0:07:22.56,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,You pretended to come and save Nel,\Nbut you just came to pick on Nel!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.88,0:07:25.28,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! I get it. Don't cry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.92,0:07:28.04,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take you with me,\Nso give me a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.20,0:07:31.80,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Good?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.56,0:07:34.52,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichi...go!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.56,0:07:36.36,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.80,0:07:38.56,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,You ended up crying again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.32,0:07:40.76,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,What are they doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.40,0:07:42.80,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,They're doing a stand-up routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.96,0:07:45.76,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.80,0:07:48.64,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear it coming from above us!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.76,0:07:49.88,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.48,0:07:53.68,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.84,0:07:55.08,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, jump!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.04,0:07:58.36,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Here… Blow your nose\Nand wipe away your tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.08,0:08:00.08,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Kurosaki, run!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.00,0:08:02.40,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, guys…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.48,0:08:08.60,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! Nel, you're safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.96,0:08:09.96,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.04,0:08:11.60,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me play too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.64,0:08:12.76,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Get off me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.20,0:08:14.60,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,You did it to me yet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.68,0:08:26.68,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa.\NThat was close.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.20,0:08:28.52,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,That was close.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.76,0:08:30.56,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo, are you all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.16,0:08:36.52,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.12,0:08:39.60,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, let's get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.72,0:08:40.88,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.48,0:08:44.12,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see if there are other stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.96,0:08:46.56,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you guys! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.44,0:08:50.36,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,It sure is dark here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.28,0:08:53.76,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,For times like this,\Njust leave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.00,0:08:56.44,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? Can you do\Nsomething about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.24,0:09:01.48,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,When tweaked a bit,\Nkido can be used like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.92,0:09:03.36,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Shakkaho!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.28,0:09:13.24,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? That's a pretty small light.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.52,0:09:16.32,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think that\Nyou were so reserved.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.56,0:09:20.36,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Fool! This happened because\Nhe tried to look cool
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.37,0:09:22.44,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,by using an Eishohaki\Neven though he's not good at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.84,0:09:24.32,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.64,0:09:26.96,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,We can follow the brightness\Nof your red hair!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.28,0:09:29.44,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,There's even a song about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.88,0:09:33.28,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,A reindeer with a bright red nose\Nbecomes useful to Santa…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.32,0:09:34.32,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.20,0:09:40.84,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.48,0:09:44.92,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Say… Did this place exist\Nbefore Aizen came?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.16,0:09:46.16,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.20,0:09:51.20,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Aizen built the building above,\Nbut I don't know about the basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.60,0:09:54.92,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,This area was probably\Nthe old building.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.16,0:09:56.92,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably not used now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.48,0:09:59.12,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Well… I don't care either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.36,0:10:01.00,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go upstairs\Nas soon as possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.28,0:10:07.04,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Something just shined!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.08,0:10:08.68,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? I didn't see anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.96,0:10:11.32,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,– I'm going to go check!\N– All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.36,0:10:12.52,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.32,0:10:17.28,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.64,0:10:18.64,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.80,0:10:22.28,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,This has got to be the exit!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.32,0:10:25.40,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed… The materials\Nused to make it are different.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.36,0:10:29.28,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything from this point on\Nmust be the newly constructed building.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.36,0:10:33.00,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, it's not\Nabandoned like this area is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.28,0:10:34.76,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,It's being used now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.28,0:10:37.24,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,We should be cautious\Nfrom this point on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.76,0:10:39.20,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,– We don't know what--\N– Ishida!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.36,0:10:41.24,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Move aside for a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.32,0:10:52.20,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! There are stairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.72,0:10:54.84,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Another door.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.00,0:10:57.00,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Kurosaki, you should\Nbe a little more--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.04,0:10:59.64,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,We just have to smash through\Nand move on!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.96,0:11:14.16,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,We finally came to\Na decent-looking place!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.00,0:11:24.28,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,A crossroad, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.60,0:11:26.92,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,What a troublesome\Nplace to come to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.16,0:11:38.76,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Nel…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.72,0:11:41.32,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.16,0:11:44.96,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like we'll have to\Npart ways here after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.36,0:11:46.16,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.44,0:11:49.00,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't seem like you guys\Nwill be able to withstand
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.04,0:11:51.20,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,the Spiritual Pressure\Nfrom this point on!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.64,0:11:55.96,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't even imagine what\Nmight happen from here on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.00,0:12:07.32,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,There are five paths.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.56,0:12:10.20,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got to check each one,\Nstarting from the ones on the ends!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.64,0:12:11.24,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,No…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.64,0:12:14.04,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go down separate paths\Nat the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.20,0:12:21.88,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying?!\NWe're talking about Espada!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.40,0:12:25.16,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be better\Nif we move together!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.44,0:12:28.08,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,If we become separated…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.12,0:12:29.12,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.52,0:12:34.60,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,It's insulting for a warrior to be concerned\Nabout his life while in the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.12,0:12:43.36,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo… You say that because\Nyou are worried about me,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.20,0:12:45.64,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,but it is not like you\Nto say something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.20,0:12:50.24,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you that you\Ndon't need to worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.24,0:12:54.48,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't come here so\Nyou would be worried about me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.60,0:13:00.80,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,All right…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.64,0:13:03.32,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go down separate paths.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.88,0:13:07.48,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.12,0:13:11.36,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, before we leave,\Nlet's chant a charm!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.64,0:13:12.24,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,A charm?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.64,0:13:17.56,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah… It's a traditional Thirteen\NCourt Guard Squads ritual of sorts
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.60,0:13:19.24,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,that’s done before big battles.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.52,0:13:23.16,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fallen out of use. There aren't\Nmany squads that do it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.68,0:13:26.76,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,But I figure it's something\Nto do at times like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.20,0:13:29.16,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!\NPlace your hands together!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.36,0:13:31.52,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't look so unenthusiastic!\NI don't really want to do it either!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.28,0:13:41.56,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going into battle now!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.92,0:13:44.40,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Believe...that our blades\Ncannot be broken!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.92,0:13:47.28,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Believe...that our hearts\Nwill not yield!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.80,0:13:51.72,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we lose our way,\Nour iron will is one!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.68,0:13:58.96,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Vow...that even if the earth splits,\Nwe will come back to this place alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.58,0:14:19.78,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,They left…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.94,0:14:21.66,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.78,0:14:22.78,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.98,0:14:27.86,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,If we turn back now,\Nit'll still be dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.78,0:14:30.38,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.58,0:14:31.74,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going, Nel?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.70,0:14:35.54,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo… Nel is going after Ichigo!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.78,0:14:38.26,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Going after him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.50,0:14:39.10,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Nel had…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.70,0:14:42.14,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Nel had fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.38,0:14:44.70,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Nel had lots and lots of fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.22,0:14:45.82,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Nel still…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.86,0:14:48.86,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Nel still want to stay with\NIchigo and the others!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.82,0:14:50.86,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,– Nel!\N– What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.78,0:14:53.22,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! We're…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.26,0:14:54.70,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,We’re going too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.18,0:15:05.82,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Which way did Nel go?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.98,0:15:19.94,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lord Aizen and his desires.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.14,0:15:23.30,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}She only hesitated\Nfor an instant.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.22,0:15:26.98,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}She didn't flinch at my question.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.30,0:15:30.58,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}She's a tough woman.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.82,0:15:33.82,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.62,0:15:38.22,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,How is our pet doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.66,0:15:40.66,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Nnoitora…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.02,0:15:46.62,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that Lord Aizen has left you\Nin charge of that woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.10,0:15:48.82,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,How wonderful…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.26,0:15:51.74,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,So? How far have\Nyou disciplined her?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.86,0:15:55.86,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,How vulgar.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.26,0:15:59.18,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get too crabby…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.46,0:16:02.58,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just asking you\Nif things are going well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.02,0:16:03.82,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.78,0:16:05.78,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,You're curious?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.70,0:16:08.82,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,That's such a trifling matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.26,0:16:09.86,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.94,0:16:12.06,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.78,0:16:15.86,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,That woman was under\NLord Aizen’s spell
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.87,0:16:18.38,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,before she came\Nto Hueco Mundo.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.78,0:16:20.78,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,His Kyokasuigetsu, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.98,0:16:24.54,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not. There's no need for him\Nto use it for something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.34,0:16:29.86,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,He placed her in several psychological\Ncages when he brought her here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.14,0:16:32.74,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,He ordered her to surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.78,0:16:35.50,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,and made her unable to refuse\Nby using her friends' lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.26,0:16:39.94,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterwards, he gave her\Na 12-hour reprieve
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.98,0:16:42.70,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,and allowed her to say good-bye\Nto one of her friends
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.74,0:16:45.86,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,on the condition that\Nno one else could notice her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.54,0:16:48.18,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,You call that a cage?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.46,0:16:51.78,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,By giving her a reprieve,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.82,0:16:56.18,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,and allowing her to say good-bye\Nto a friend in such a tense situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.78,0:17:00.70,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,she'll mistakenly believe that\Nwe've shown her sympathy
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.74,0:17:02.02,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,and her feelings will\Nwaver a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.22,0:17:10.46,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,But her friends' lives were not actually\Nat risk during that 12-hour reprieve.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.26,0:17:13.58,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, even though\Nshe was forced to surrender…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.62,0:17:15.90,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,By allowing her to choose\Nsomeone to say good-bye to,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.94,0:17:19.30,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,she'd get the idea that\Nshe had done so by choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.86,0:17:24.90,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterwards, by making her\Ncome to a specified place
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.82,0:17:27.78,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,before taking her\Nto Hueco Mundo
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.70,0:17:32.02,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,that idea would be etched\Neven deeper into her mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.42,0:17:34.98,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,She'd gradually lose\Nthe will to run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.70,0:17:37.30,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.38,0:17:42.18,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,The fact that we allowed her to\Nsay good-bye to only one person
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.22,0:17:43.30,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,without anyone else noticing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.86,0:17:49.58,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,means that she'd leave evidence of\Nhaving said good-bye to only one person.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.98,0:17:51.22,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,What of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.22,0:17:55.58,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,We've failed if\Nyou let her do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.90,0:17:56.90,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Quite the opposite…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.18,0:18:00.90,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,The evidence of having said good-bye\Nbecomes undeniable proof
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.94,0:18:05.82,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,that she was free to do\Nwhat she wanted until she surrendered.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.30,0:18:09.30,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.70,0:18:12.78,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,The stronger the evidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.54,0:18:18.66,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,the more her friends would think\Nthat she willfully betrayed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.34,0:18:27.38,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,That last part wasn't\Na complete success.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.02,0:18:32.86,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's safe to say that Soul Society\Nisn't getting involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.82,0:18:35.74,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,That sure was well thought out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.46,0:18:38.78,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that's to be\Nexpected of Lord Aizen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.86,0:18:41.66,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Well thought out?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.74,0:18:46.34,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a game to Lord Aizen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.50,0:18:50.54,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,It would have been fine whether\Nshe played into it or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.70,0:18:52.78,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever the case…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.10,0:18:56.22,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, that woman has\Nno strength to run away from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.70,0:19:01.46,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,She doesn't have the will\Nor strength to defy us either.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.78,0:19:07.78,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad you've come…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.74,0:19:09.54,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Orihime.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.42,0:19:13.94,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry I called you here\Non such short notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.06,0:19:17.34,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something\NI want to show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.78,0:19:21.70,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Loly, Menoly, leave us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.42,0:19:23.02,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.50,0:19:27.22,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But we cannot leave someone\Nlike her alone with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.78,0:19:31.74,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,– E-Excuse us!\N– E-Excuse us!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.78,0:19:35.50,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that woman?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.82,0:19:39.82,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.14,0:19:43.70,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you take a look at this,\NOrihime?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.54,0:19:59.66,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What is this sensation?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.26,0:20:03.10,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Could this be...?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.62,0:20:04.70,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems you can tell…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.50,0:20:06.74,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Hogyoku.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.22,0:20:13.22,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a little weak from repetitive\Ninstantaneous awakenings,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.70,0:20:16.70,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's definitely becoming\Nfully awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.86,0:20:21.54,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Without the Hogyoku,\Nit is impossible to either
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.58,0:20:24.10,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,transform Hollows into Arrancars,\Nor create the Ouken.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.34,0:20:30.10,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Consider the fact that I showed this\Nto you as proof that I trust you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.94,0:20:34.22,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,You have the power of\Nphenomenon rejection.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.22,0:20:37.66,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,You can negate things\Nthat have happened
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.70,0:20:39.78,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,and wipe out the events entirely.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.74,0:20:42.26,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an incredible power.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.38,0:20:45.58,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,I need your power…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.74,0:20:47.54,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Orihime.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.46,0:20:53.26,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll use your power for me,\Nwon't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.62,0:21:03.74,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't think he showed me\Nthe Hogyoku because he trusts me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.82,0:21:08.02,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I at least know\Nwhere the Hogyoku is.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.78,0:21:11.38,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And about my power…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.74,0:21:17.86,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can negate things that have happened\Nand wipe out the events entirely.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.74,0:21:22.62,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Thank you for coming\Nto save me Kurosaki.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.50,0:21:26.70,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I know what\NI have to do here.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.86,0:21:30.78,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's probably something\Nthat only I can do.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.34,0:21:35.22,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I have to use my power to\Nreturn the Hogyoku{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.26,0:21:37.46,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}back to the state it was in\Nbefore it existed!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.42,0:23:23.78,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Renji, have you ever\Ndone that cheer before?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.82,0:23:25.94,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I've suggested it to\Nmy captain several times,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.98,0:23:27.66,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,but for some reason\Nhe always ignores me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.98,0:23:30.10,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Rukia, ask him to do it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.14,0:23:31.46,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Well…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.58,0:23:33.82,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think that\NByakuya would do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.58,0:23:37.74,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,THE ARRANCAR ENCYCLOPEDIA\NThe Arrancar Encyclopedia.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.82,0:23:42.22,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Today I shall reveal my secrets!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.90,0:23:44.70,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,First, my Dondochakka Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.82,0:23:48.30,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,They're sharp eyes that can find\Nmy targets in games of eternal pursuit!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.38,0:23:49.74,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,My Dondochakka Innards!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.78,0:23:52.58,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a wonderful stomach\Nthat can digest anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.86,0:23:54.42,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Shoot 'im dead, Shinso!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.38,0:23:57.14,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.18,0:23:59.78,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez…\NYou took over my segment.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.74,0:24:02.34,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,But this is pretty amusing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.70,0:24:04.78,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe next time\NI'll try this with someone.